solutions.content:
# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We will convert the list into the list with dummy head and dummy tail. It will help us to maintain pointer and will save us from writing edge cases for null pointers.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Eg. Given list is `1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 4`. We will convert it to `-1 -> 1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 4 -> -1`. Now our head will point to dummy head.

We will keep track of three pointer and will reverse every pair of elements,
1. prev - which will link the reversed element (from a pair of elements), this pointer is immediate left of the current pair
2. cur - first element of current pair
3. next - second element of current pair

If we look at this example `-1 -> 1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 4 -> -1`, then in the first iteration prev would be -1, cur would be 1 and next would be 2.

After swapping a pair list will look like this `-1 -> 2 -> 1 -> 3 -> 4 -> -1`. Now we will have our next pair which is `3 -> 4`. So prev would be 1, curr would be at 3 and next would be at 4. 

After second iteration list will look like `-1 -> 2 -> 1 -> 4 -> 3 -> -1`.

Now, The list is swapped in pairs of two elements. We just have to remove dummy head and dummy tail.

Final answer: `2 -> 1 -> 4 -> 3`

**NOTE 1:** ***Odd size list handled in the code. Just emit the last element from being swapped with dummy tail.***
**NOTE 2:** ***Code is self explanatory.***

### Iteration Steps Explanation
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/2deeb1b9-a52a-4694-9bbd-6e681c855146_1684217143.7158692.png)

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
    - As we are traversing list only once (ignore adding and deleting dummy head and dummy tail)

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$
    - As we have not used any space (containers) except the pointers.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* swapPairs(ListNode* head) {
        // if list is null or contains one element then return the list itself (null => null & `1` => `1`)
        if (!head or !head->next)
            return head;

        // Adding dummy head
        ListNode *dummyHead = new ListNode(-1);
        dummyHead->next = head;
        head = dummyHead;

        // Adding dummy tail
        ListNode *dummyTail = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode *ptr = head;
        while (ptr->next)
            ptr = ptr->next;
        ptr->next = dummyTail;

        // assigning prev, cur and next for first iteration
        ListNode *prev = head, *cur = head->next, *next = head->next->next;
        while (next and next->val != -1)
        {
            // Check above image
            ListNode *nextCur = next->next; // 1
            prev->next = next; // 2
            cur->next = next->next; // 3
            next->next = cur; // 4

            prev = cur; // 5
            cur = nextCur; // 6
            next = cur->next; // 7
        }   

        // Remove dummy tail
        ListNode *remove = head;
        while(remove->next->val != -1)
            remove = remove->next;
        remove->next = NULL;

        // remove dummy head
        return head = head->next;
    }
};
```
