# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Here we are using a very simple and easy ***recursive*** approach to solve this


**Steps:**

1. At first we will check, if head value is null we will return null.

    `if(head==null) return null;`
2. Then we check, if next head value is null we will return current head.

    `if (head.next == null) return head;`
3. Later we will swap the 2 value of by creating a temp variable & recursively swapping the values.

    - Storing the next head to a temp ListNode that we will return at last. `ListNode temp = head.next;`
    - Then we  get the call the function recursively for next head. 
     `head.next = swapPairs(temp.next);`
    - Then we swap value next temp with the head.
     `temp.next = head;`
4. At last we will return the temp ListNode we created .

    `return temp;`

